HIV/AIDS: China ta ce an samu karuwar kashi 14 cikin 100 na sabon kamuwa da cutar
Kasar Sin ta ce an samu karuwar mutane 14 cikin 100 da ke dauke da cutar HIV da AIDS.
Jami'an lafiya sun ce, a kasar akwai mutane fiye da 820,000 da suka kamu da cutar.
A cikin kwata na biyu na shekarar 2018 kadai, an samu karin mutane 40,000.
Yawancin sabbin cututtuka suna kamuwa da jima'i, wanda ke nuna canji daga baya.
A wasu sassan kasar Sin, an yi amfani da jinin mutanen da suka kamu da cutar don yada cutar ta HIV.
Amma, a wani taron da aka gudanar a lardin Yunnan, jami'an lafiya na kasar Sin sun ce, an yi kusan rage yawan mutanen da ke dauke da cutar HIV ta wannan hanyar.
Duk da haka, a ƙasar Sin, adadin mutanen da ke kamuwa da cutar HIV da AIDS yana ƙaruwa da miliyan ɗaya a kowace shekara.
Yada cutar HIV ta hanyar jima'i a tsakanin LGBT al'ummomin kasar Sin babbar matsala ce.
A shekarar 1997, kasar Sin ta kawar da laifin gay, amma har yanzu tana nuna bambanci ga LGBT.
Saboda ci gaba da kasancewa da dabi'u masu mahimmanci a cikin ƙasar, nazarin ya nuna cewa 70-90% na maza da ke yin jima'i da maza zasu auri mata a ƙarshe.
A yawancin lokaci, ana samun cututtuka ta hanyar rashin samun isasshen kariya ta jima'i a lokacin da maza ke yin jima'i da juna.
A matsayin wani ɓangare na ƙoƙarin magance wannan matsalar, tun daga shekara ta 2003, gwamnatin Sin ta yi alkawarin samar da magungunan cutar HIV a ko'ina.
