Jakadan Amurka ya zargi kasar Sin da yin barazanar amfani da 'tallace-tallace'
Wata mako bayan da wata jarida ta kasar Sin ta wallafa wata sanarwa mai shafuka hudu a wata jarida ta Amurka game da nasarorin da kasar Sin ta samu a kan cinikayya tsakanin Amurka da China, jakadan Amurka a kasar Sin ya zargi Beijing da amfani da kafofin watsa labarai na Amurka wajen yada labaran kasar Sin.
A cikin jaridar Des Moines Register - jaridar da ta fi kowa sayarwa a jihar Iowa - shugaban Amurka ya yi magana game da ƙarin da China Daily ya bayar game da zargin da ake yi wa kasar Sin na ƙoƙarin tsoma baki a zaben Amurka na ranar 6 ga watan Nuwamba.
Jami'an Amurka sun shaida wa Reuters cewa zargin da Trump ya yi na cewa Beijing na kokarin tsoma baki a zaben Amurka, wani sabon mataki ne a cikin kara karfin yakin neman zaben Washington na matsa lamba a kan kasar Sin.
Ko da yake yana da kyau a yi amfani da tallace-tallace na kasashen waje don inganta kasuwanci, dangantakar da ke tsakanin Beijing da Washington ta shiga cikin rikici mai tsanani na kasuwanci, inda kasashen biyu ke ƙara shigo da kayayyakin da suke shigo da su daga juna.
A lokacin yakin cinikayya, masana tattalin arziki a China da Amurka sun ce, a baya, China ta kara yawan shigo da kayayyaki a Amurka, kuma an tsara sabon haraji ne don yin niyya ga kamfanonin shigo da kayayyaki a jihohi kamar Iowa, wadanda ke goyon bayan Jam'iyyar Republican na Trump.
